spp_who: initials of who entered the data
ID_new: unique ID for each reference; column used to merge to all other tables
source: where in the paper one extracted such information
external_trt: external treatment applied to the nutrient treatment (e.g, water, CO2, parasites)
reponse_var: define which response variable data is added; e.g., biomass, sla, root:shoot
site: site of study, if there are multiple
spp_biomass: specify which species response data is being entered for
f_nat_inv: focal plant is native or invasive or na
c_nat_inv: competitior plant is native or invasive or na
c_#indiv: competitior plant number of individuals; if multiple comp spp, add # of indiv per spp separated by ;
biomass_type: AGB + BGB or AGB or BGB or unclear or NA [if response var other than biomass]
response_mean: response value of plant species at specific nutrient value
response_transformation: response value of plant species at specific nutrient value
response_mean_unit: response unit of plant species at specific nutrient value.
response_var_unit: response variance unit e.g., se, sd, ci
sample_size: number of replicates e.g., no of pots, plots, transects
nutrient_general: e.g, N; P; K etc [use ; to separate words]
nutrient_compound: e.g, NO3; KHPO4 [use ; to separate words]
nutrient_interval_days: how frequently nutrient was added in days, 1 or 4 or 15 or 30 etc
nutrient_addition_duration: total duration of nutrient addition (in days)
